HC 13—RC 2506/DI hf

February 2, 2026
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
HOUSE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. 13
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION urging the United States
2 Congress to require the United States Secretary of State to
3 designate the Muslim Brotherhood as a foreign terrorist
4 organization.
5 Whereas, The federal government has the authority and
6 responsibility under federal law to identify and respond to
7 threats posed by organizations engaged in terrorist activities;
8 Whereas, Section 219 of the Immigration and Nationality Act
9 (8 U.S.C. 1189) establishes the process by which the United
10 States Secretary of State designates foreign terrorist
11 organizations;
12 Whereas, The Muslim Brotherhood is a transnational Sunni
13 Islamist organization founded in Egypt in 1928, with branches
14 and affiliates throughout the Middle East and Africa;
15 Whereas, Various national security assessments and
16 international observers have linked certain branches and
17 affiliates of the Muslim Brotherhood to extremist ideology,
18 support for violence, and groups that have carried out terrorist
19 acts;
20 Whereas, Several countries, including Egypt, the Kingdom of
21 Saudi Arabia, and the United Arab Emirates, have designated
22 the Muslim Brotherhood or its affiliates as a terrorist
23 organization; and
24 Whereas, A formal designation by the United States would
25 allow federal authorities to apply the statutory tools associated
26 with the designation of a foreign terrorist organization
HC 13—RC 2506/DI hf

2
1 designation under Section 219 of the Immigration and
2 Nationality Act to organizations determined to be engaged in
3 terrorist activity: Therefore,
4 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives
5 of the General Assembly of the State of Indiana,
6 the Senate concurring:
7 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly supports
8 federal action from the United States Congress requiring the
9 Secretary of State to designate the Muslim Brotherhood as a
10 foreign terrorist organization pursuant to Section 219 of the
11 Immigration and Nationality Act.
12 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
13 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to
14 Representative Christopher Judy for distribution.
HC 13—RC 2506/DI hf

